snippet.title: Head, Shoulders, Knees And Toes Nursery Rhyme | Exercise Song For Kids
snippet.description:
Heads Shoulders Knees and Toes is a nursery rhymes song that does its bit in educating us about the different parts of our human body. Kids! We know. Your parents know. Your teachers know. Your family knows. That you’ll love to sing and dance and jump and do a whole lot of fun activities with your kiddie songs. So, through this video for toddlers, let’s take couple of minutes of our playtime to understand which part of the body helps do what. Like the knees and toes, which are part of our legs help us jump. The hands help us form postures and maintain balance while dancing. The mouth helps us sing our classic baby songs. The eyes light up and tell everyone that we’re happy to do the routine. There are many more parts of our body, which we need to learn about with this baby song. And our hands help us click the play button, too!

snippet.description:

Summer is coming and Nicolas wants to get fit and has began his training, running, weight lifting, push ups, squats, abs, cycling, yoga. A kids workout routine is hard so he always changes his exercises, sometimes he throws toys, make a mess, take out our clothes from the drawer, anything that makes him happy. snippet.title: Yoga Exercise For Kids Growth & Height - Treatment, Asana, Tips & Cure in Hindi
snippet.description:
Yoga is a way of living. Yoga is not only a exercise but it also helps to lead a good and healthy life, making you look good and stay happy. We introduce, Yogacharya Shree Avneesh Tiwari, who have been practicing yoga from past 40 years and have travelled all over India to teach yoga. With the help of these yoga videos by Acharaya, you will not only learn yoga asanas but also right way of leading your life. 

(1) Tadasana which is also known as mountain pose. It has many benefits.

1: Improves posture.
2: Increases strength.
3: Improves blood circulation.
4: Increases height.
5: Firms abdomen.

(2) Triyak tadasana which is also known as side bend pose. it has many benefits. 

1: Decrease back pains.
2: Cleanses and tones the entire intestinal area.
3: Reduces waist.
4: Reduces obesity.

(3) Katichakrasana which is also known as spinal twist.

1: Good for relieving constipation.
2: Good for arm and leg muscles.
3: Burns belly fat.
4: Increases balance.

(4) Padahastasana which is also known as hand to foot pose. It has many benefits.

1: Stretches hamstring muscles.
2: Increases flexibility.
3: Stimulates internal organs.
4: Reduces belly fat.

(5) Sarvangasana which is also known as shoulder stand pose. It has many benefits.

1: Helps boost self- confidence.
2: Tones abdomen area.
3: Strengthens shoulders.
4: Calms mind and body.
5: Reduces depression and develops patience.

(6) Halasana which is also known as plough pose. It has many health benefits.

1: Stretches leg muscles.
2: Helps in digestion.
3: Improves flexibility.
4: Improves shoulder strength.
5: Strengthens spine.

(7) Chakrasana which is also known as wheel pose. It has many benefits.

1: Stimulates internal organs.
2: Strengthens back.
3: Relieves stress.
4: Tones abdominal muscle.

(8) Nadishodhan pranayam which is also known as alternate nostril breathing. It has many health benefits. 

1: Relieves stress and anxiety.
2: Calms mind and soul.
3: Helps fight asthma.
4: Keeps heart healthy.

snippet.title: Child's Pose with T-spine Mobilization - Stick Mobility Exercise
snippet.description:
This variation of the Child’s Pose provides thoracic extension and opens up and mobilizes the shoulders and lats. Helps reduce the negative effects of sitting for long periods of time, such as rounding of the spine. T-spine and shoulder mobility play a crucial role in your ability to perform well not only on the playing field, but in everyday life. Simple tasks like reaching, picking and lifting things up, and even breathing are affected by poor spinal mobility. The stiffer the spine or more rounded the posture, the less your ribs are able to expand properly. So give this single short stick (4-5ft) drill a try and start moving and breathing better!

------- 

Stick Mobility is a training system that improves your mobility, stability, and strength.

The exercises combine joint mobilization, strength training, and deep fascial stretching to increase athletic performance, reduce the risk of injury, and speed recovery after exercise.

The system uses the Mobility Stick as a simple tool to improve range of motion, muscle activation, coordination, and body awareness to build a strong foundation for better movement. It provides kinesthetic and visual feedback to users and coaches. The Mobility Stick is made with a custom blend of materials designed to achieve the balance of flexibility, strength, and grip needed for the full range of Stick Mobility exercises.

The exercises are based on the scientific principles of:

– Leverage
– Stability
– Feedback
– Irradiation
– Isometrics
– Coordination

To learn more about the program, find classes, workshops, certification courses, and to buy Mobility Sticks check out: http://www.stickmobility.com

Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/stickmobility

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/stickmobility/

snippet.title: Children Do Not Do Enough Exercise
snippet.description:
Half of all seven-year-olds do not get enough exercise - with girls far less active than boys according to new research.

Only 51% of all seven-year-olds in the UK achieve the recommended hour of exercise every day.

The figure breaks down to just 38% of girls hitting the target, compared with 63% in boys.

Half of this age group is also sedentary for an average of 6.4 hours or more every day, experts have found.

The research, published in the online journal BMJ Open, found that children of Indian origin and those living in Northern Ireland are among the least physically active of all seven-year-olds.

snippet.title: Dyseggxia - an exercise tool for children with Dyslexia
snippet.description:
Dyseggxia is a mobile game that helps children with Dyslexia by the means of fun word games. All exercises in Dyseggxia have been scientifically designed to target reading and writing errors specific for Dyslexic children.

The exercises have been evaluated by a group of users with Dyslexia and are targeted to help improve difficulties caused by Dyslexia. To do so, we have combined current pedagogical strategies with the results of an analysis of real errors made by children.

Dyseggxia is divided into three levels: easy, medium and hard. These have been designed according to word frequency in texts, word length and the number of similar words.

Each level contains several exercises from 5 types:

- Insertion: a letter is missing in a word and must be inserted from the available answers
- Omission: there is an extra letter in the word that must be deleted
- Substitution: there is a wrong letter in the word that must be changed by one of the possible answers
- Derivation: the user is presented with several possible endings to a word and must chose the correct option
- Sentence separation: several words are put together, and the user must identify the breaking points between words

Dyseggxia now includes exercises both in Spanish and English! Easily choose the language you want to play with in the home screen.
